list.abstract: industry（英 [ˈɪndəstri]，美 [ˈɪndəstri]），英语单词，作名词为工业；产业；大型研究活动。例句：The setbacks in the eggs industry.（鸡蛋行业的挫折。） industry的近义词有domain等。形容词有industrial。

yingyinNormal.en: It's an industry worth an estimated $1.5 billion a year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是个每年创造大约十五亿美元产值的工业。

yingyinNormal.en: The device I'm about to introduce to you is gonna revolutionize an entire industry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我正要介绍给你们的这个设备将会引发整个工业界的一场革命。

yingyinNormal.en: This is what America's auto industry looked like in 1980. Each dot is a factory run by a U.S. automaker.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就像是1980年时的美国汽车工业，每个汽车工厂都是美国经营的。

yingyinNormal.en: That's six times more than any other country. But historically, this enormous industry has been plagued by inefficiency.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是其他国家的六倍，但是历史上这一大工业曾被低效率困扰着。

yingyinNormal.en: This is the Queen's award for industry. Thank you. Keep up the good work. Three cheers for Miss Rabbit.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是女王为工业颁发的奖项！谢谢！继续保持优秀的工作，让我们给兔子小姐三声欢呼！

yingyinNormal.en: More jobs, more insured, a growing economy, Shrinking deficits, bustling industry, booming energy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 更多的就业岗位，更多的投保人，不断增长的经济，削减中的赤字，蒸蒸日上的工业，蓬勃发展中的能源产业。

yingyinNormal.en: This is the Queen's award for industry. Thank you. Keep up the good work. Three cheers for Miss Rabbit. Hip, hip. Hooray. Hip, hip. Hooray. Hip. Hip. Hip. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是女王为工业颁发的奖项！谢谢！继续保持优秀的工作，让我们给兔子小姐三声欢呼！耶！好耶！耶，耶！好耶！耶！耶！耶！好耶！

yingyinNormal.en: It's a term that came out of the car industry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这来自于汽车行业。

yingyinNormal.en: If an industry can not live more than 3 years, if all the companies can not live happily for 3 years, this industry is(will) never become the mainstream.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果一个行业不能活得超过3年，如果不是所有的公司能够快乐地生存超过3年，那这个行业永远无法成为主流。

yingyinNormal.en: In aerospace, the military, we will own the entire robotics industry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这可以应用在航太和军事我们将称霸机器人产业。

yingyinNormal.en: But we chose to invest in American auto industry and American workers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但我们选择投资于美国的汽车产业和美国的产业工人。

yingyinNormal.en: Your earth is a very small part of a very large industry. Feel my skin.
yingyinNormal.zh: 地球只是一个大企业体系中的一小部份。摸摸我的皮肤。

yingyinNormal.en: The auto industry we rescued is on track for its strongest year since 2005.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们所拯救的汽车产业正处于自2005年以来最好的时候。

yingyinNormal.en: It's been a major boost to our economy and a profound change to our auto industry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 成为了我们经济的巨大推动力量，并促进了我国汽车行业的深化改革。

yingyinNormal.en: And in the 1980s, America's steel industry simply collapsed, costing over 300,000 jobs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在80年代美国钢产业倒闭了，空出来300000多个工作岗位。

yingyinNormal.en: America was built on the spirit of industry. You build your future. It isn't handed to you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 美国的根基是勤劳精神，未来靠自己努力，而非靠人施予。

yingyinNormal.en: The government will then send Sacks Industry a blank check and I'm going to be rich, like, stupid rich.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后政府就将会给萨克斯集团， 一张任我填写的支票，之后我就会变富有， 非常的富有。

yingyinNormal.en: Sure, most of the leaders in every industry were men, but we thought changing that was just a matter of time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，大部分行业的领袖都是男性。但改变应该只是时间问题。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: This industry can never become the deep economy, so, what we want to do is that how we can find this solution.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个行业永远不可能深深根植于经济，所以，我们要做什么才能找到解决方案?

yingyinNormal.en: The food industry is in the business of creating desirable commodities, and we're in the business of eating a lot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 食品业就是为了制造吸引顾客的商品，而我们的工作就是吃。大吃特吃。

word_usage.usage: industry的基本意思是“工业”，用作工业的总称时,是不可数名词，不加冠词，指“具体的某类工业或行业”时是可数名词，通常加冠词。
industry也可表示为“各行业”，如the fashion industry（时尚行业）。一般情况下，单用industry，指的是“工业”，而非“行业”；表示某种“工业”或“行业”时，常用动词establish，build up或develop来表示开办或建立该行业，如establish the food industry建立食品行业。

examination_example.sentence: A restructuring of the textbook <highlight>industry</highlight> may well be in order. But this does not mean the end of the textbook itself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教科书产业重组势在必行，但这也并不意味着教科书本身的终结。

examination_example.sentence: Textbooks represent an 11 billion dollar <highlight>industry</highlight>, up from $8 billion in 2014.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教科书是一个价值高达110亿美元的产业，2014年时其产业价值为80亿美元。

examination_example.sentence: There have been concerns around the sugar content of cereal and the food <highlight>industry's</highlight> involvement in pro-breakfast research — and even one claim from an academic that breakfast is "dangerous".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们也一直担心谷物中的糖分含量，以及食品行业参与的支持早餐的研究，甚至有学者声称，早餐是“危险的”。

examination_example.sentence: At times, these breaks and transitions will be self-determined, at others they will be forced as existing roles, firms, or <highlight>industries</highlight> cease to exist.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有时，这些休息和过渡是自主决定的，有时则是由于现有的角色、公司或行业不复存在而被迫进行的。

examination_example.sentence: Aydin Municipality bought the plane from a private company for just under US$100,000, but they hope to see a return on that investment through the tourism <highlight>industry</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 艾丁市以不到十万美元的价格从一家私人公司购买了这架飞机，但他们希望通过旅游业获得投资回报。

examination_example.sentence: If you factor in the projected rates of technological change, either your skills will become unnecessary, or your <highlight>industry</highlight> outdated.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果将技术的预计变革速率考虑在内，要么你的技能变得多余，要么你所在的行业将会过时。

examination_example.sentence: Levels of outdoor pollution have grown rapidly along with rapid growth in <highlight>industry</highlight> and transportation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着工业和交通的快速增长，室外污染水平迅速上升。

examination_example.sentence: Shifting eating habits, including a sharp drop in consumption of sparkling drinks, have forced radical change on the <highlight>industry</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 饮食习惯的转变，包括气泡饮料消费量的急剧下降，迫使该行业发生了根本性的变化。

examination_example.sentence: The maker of Mountain Dew and Gatorade has been one of the earlier movers in the <highlight>industry</highlight> to offer products with reduced levels of unhealthy ingredients.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 激浪(Mountain Dew)和佳得乐(Gatorad)的制造商是行业内较早提供减少不健康成分的产品的企业之一。

examination_example.sentence: This is similar to what's happening in the coal and oil <highlight>industries</highlight>, a situation that fuels much of the current political discontent in this country.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这类似于煤炭和石油行业中发生的情况，这种情况加剧了该国当前的许多政治不满情绪。

examination_example.sentence: The city's current mayor, Luigi Brugnaro, has ridiculed UNESCO and told it to mind its own business, while continuing to support the cruise ship <highlight>industry</highlight>, which employs 5, 000 Venice residents.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 威尼斯现任市长 Luigi Brugnaro 嘲笑联合国教科文组织(UNESCO)，让它管好自己的事，同时继续支持雇用了5000名威尼斯居民的游轮业。

examination_example.sentence: The textbook <highlight>industry</highlight> insists the online systems represent a better deal for students.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教科书行业坚持认为，在线系统对学生而言是更好的选择。
